7.1.8 - M365SR08: Exposure of Synchronised Active Directory Information
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1507; Revision: 3; Updated: Dec-23; Applicability: All; OS: All (Privileged access to cloud services is performed through a secure gateway or workstation)
•	Control: 0957; Revision: 7; Updated: Sep-23; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting access to systems and applications)
•	Control: 1563; Revision: 0; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting access to cloud services based on risk)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Active Directory information within the agency domain is being regularly synchronised with Azure Active Directory (Entra ID). Adversaries may gain access to the agency's Active Directory information should they gain access to the agency Azure Tenant, compromising the integrity and confidentiality of agency information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
POSSIBLE	x	MAJOR	=	HIGH
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Limit Synchronisation Scope: Configure Microsoft Entra Connect to only synchronise the minimum necessary attributes and Organisational Units (OUs) required for cloud operations, excluding sensitive on-premises metadata.
2.	Enforce Strict Tenant Administrative Controls: Protect the cloud-side identity plane by mandating phishing-resistant MFA and Privileged Identity Management (PIM) for all roles capable of viewing or modifying directory data.
3.	Implement Hybrid Identity Protection: Deploy Microsoft Entra ID Protection and Defender for Identity to detect lateral movement or anomalous directory enumeration across both the on-premises and cloud environments.
- Treatment #1
•	Attribute Filtering: Review and customise the Entra ID Connect sync rules to filter out high-value or sensitive Active Directory attributes (e.g., employee IDs or legacy system comments) that are not functional requirements for M365.
•	Securing the Sync Server: Harden the on-premises server running Entra ID Connect as a Tier 0 asset, restricting interactive login and applying the same security rigor as a Domain Controller.
•	Continuous Monitoring: Enable diagnostic logging for Entra ID and integrate these logs with a SIEM (e.g., Microsoft Sentinel) to alert on large-scale exports or unauthorised changes to the directory schema.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
By narrowing the data surface area through attribute filtering and strictly guarding the administrative entry points to the tenant, the risk of an adversary "reaching back" or gaining meaningful intelligence from synchronised data is greatly reduced. The likelihood of an impactful compromise of directory information is lowered to "Rare."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
RARE	x	MAJOR	=	MEDIUM

